
Download/Install git;

1.
In an new folder: git init.

2. Clone:

git clone https:/**
Or	git clone username@host:/path_to_repository

// Start to use.

3. Add file

After edit the file. i.e., "vim file1"

git add <file1> //Or "git add *" to add all new files

4. Add comments

git commit -m "Message"

5. Push

git push // Or "git push origin master" for first push. Or "git remote add  origin <server>"


6. Pull

git pull

7. See all the log

git log.

For more info, visit:
http://rogerdudler.github.io/git-guide/index.zh.html





